A state takeover of the  Royal Mail ’s
pension fund generated a 28 billion-pound ($44.3 billion)
windfall for the U.K.’s budget, the Sunday Times reported,
without naming its source.  The transfer requires European Union approval, which is
expected within weeks, the London newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
